This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of medical images using fully convolutional networks. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of context information and multi-scale deep supervision could indicate that it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the fact that it deals with medical imaging could suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
